t: To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David.
The*p fool hath said in his heart, There is no God. They are corrupt, they have done abominable works, there is none that doeth good.
The*p Lord*s looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there were any that did understand, and seek God.
They*p are all gone aside, they are all together become filthy: there is none that doeth good, no, not one.
Have*p all the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eat up my people as they eat bread, and call not upon the Lord.*s
There*p were they in great fear: for God is in the generation of the righteous.
Ye*p have shamed the counsel of the poor, because the Lord*s is his refuge.
Oh*p that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion! when the Lord*s bringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel shall be glad.
